There are reports that the Alaafin of Oyo, Oba Lamidi Adeyemi, may have joined his ancestors. A formal confirmation by the Oyo Mesi and the Oyo State government has, however, not been made. The foremost Yoruba traditional ruler was one of the longest-reigning Alaafin of Oyo. He became Aláàfin in 1970. He was aged 83. Details later… ALSO READ FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE  